{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-projects-page-js","path":"/projects/being-an-islander/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>I've been lucky to work on this project with my friend and\nex-colleague Anastasia Christophilopolou over the last couple of years. She\nhas a large exhibition that will be installed in the Fitzwilliam Museum in 2023\n(substantially delayed due to pandemic working and museum management machinations). Work from\nthe AHRC funded Linking Islands of Data project and CEEF 3D fellowships were set to feed into exhibition preparation and this\nincluded:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Development of tactile 3D objects for the exhibition (we created a large 3D cast of the Dionysos of Salmis torso)</li>\n<li>Development of a Museum in a Box installation by Jennifer Wexler, which focused on Winifred Lamb and travelling objects</li>\n<li>Creation of a dedicated exhibition/research website, controlled and created by the curatorial team</li>\n<li>Enriched museum collections records - maps, metadata</li>\n</ol>\n<p>All of the above were achieved and delivered as part of our work, often with lukewarm\ninstitutional response; innovative elements were blocked from being delivered - for example\na virtual reality installation and a collaboration with a large gaming corporation - due to\nlack of vision from leadership.</p>\n<h2>Project website</h2>\n<p>The project website followed the tried and tested Egyptian Coffins project framework using\nJekyll to deliver a research component for Anastasia's work. Working together, I taught her\nhow to create, update and maintain her digital presence for the project, store images on\nthe Museum's Directus 8 instance and to be digitally independent. The website covers a wide\nvariety of aspects - team membership, research topics, archaeological information, basic exhibition\ninformation and maps.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 734px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 408.8%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/b3e8a0a400901357973eff539024b3f2/4be29/islander.webp 500w,\n/static/b3e8a0a400901357973eff539024b3f2/412eb/islander.webp 734w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 734px) 100vw, 734px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/b3e8a0a400901357973eff539024b3f2/d1f95/islander.jpg 500w,\n/static/b3e8a0a400901357973eff539024b3f2/e868b/islander.jpg 734w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 734px) 100vw, 734px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/b3e8a0a400901357973eff539024b3f2/e868b/islander.jpg\"\n            alt=\"A screenshot of the project website\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">A screenshot of the project website</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h2>Traveling objects Museum in a Box</h2>\n<p>As part of the AHRC CEEF3D fellowships, my colleague Jennifer Wexler built a collection of objects\nand content using 3d prints, voice overs (with Hannah Platts as Winifred Lamb) and other techniques to produce a box for self discovery around the themes\nfor the exhibition.</p>\n<h2>Mapping antiquity</h2>\n<p>A very quick outcome from rebuilding the collections database for the Fitzwilliam was\nthe ability to repurpose and reuse data easily. This enabled the generation of the mapping interface\nbelow, which uses geocoded archaeological objects from the Antiquities department, and provides\nfaceted access to information. This intervention made use of British Library funded Peripleo\nsoftware, and I worked with Elton Barker and Rainer Simon to create a version that suited our needs.</p>\n<div class=\"ratio ratio-1x1\">\n    <iframe src=\"https://mapping-antiquity.fitzmuseum.cam.ac.uk/#/?/?/?/mode=points\" \n        title=\"Mapping True to Nature\" \n        allowfullscreen></iframe>\n</div>","id":"8d77380d-202a-5796-99b6-73a4986082d2","timeToRead":1,"wordCount":{"words":379},"frontmatter":{"date":"October 23, 2022","section":"projects","title":"Being an Islander","description":"An overview of my involvement in the Fitzwilliam Museum Being-an-Islander project","role":null,"partners":null,"collaborators":["Anastasia Christophilopolou","Jennifer Wexler","Rainer Simon","Elton Barker","Jana Mokrišova","Ema Baužytė","Marcos Martinón-Torres","Hannah Platts"],"institution":"The Fitzwilliam Museum","publications":null,"geo_lat":52.199722,"geo_lon":0.119167,"news":null,"background":{"id":"bf41cc9b-fc6e-5aba-8edb-0525b1500068","absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/museologi.st/museologi.st/content/images/2022/islander/GR_2_1891_1_201603_mfj22_dc1.jpg","publicURL":"/static/472c32cb7d1602071bf0ef991424e29b/GR_2_1891_1_201603_mfj22_dc1.jpg","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#484848","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/472c32cb7d1602071bf0ef991424e29b/9112f/GR_2_1891_1_201603_mfj22_dc1.jpg","srcSet":"/static/472c32cb7d1602071bf0ef991424e29b/78d76/GR_2_1891_1_201603_mfj22_dc1.jpg 203w,\n/static/472c32cb7d1602071bf0ef991424e29b/5b7f1/GR_2_1891_1_201603_mfj22_dc1.jpg 406w,\n/static/472c32cb7d1602071bf0ef991424e29b/9112f/GR_2_1891_1_201603_mfj22_dc1.jpg 811w","sizes":"(min-width: 811px) 811px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/472c32cb7d1602071bf0ef991424e29b/3b9dd/GR_2_1891_1_201603